description:
&lt;p&gt;Total Wellbeing Luton was commissioned in 2018 to provide an innovative approach aiming to support both the emotional and physical health needs of people across Luton. The service brings together a range of evidence-based interventions aimed at addressing emotional health concerns through Talking Therapies early, whilst encouraging and enabling the adoption of healthier lifestyles, such as smoking cessation, weight management, increasing physical activity, and increasing quality of life in the context of long-term conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for a permanent Clinical Lead to join our team and are inviting experienced BABCP accredited CBT therapist applicants for this role. As the Clinical Lead you will be responsible for clinical leadership, supervision and advice on psychological therapies within the service. You will also lead on service development, ensure that CPD is available and research opportunities explored. We are looking for someone who understands the challenges of working in IAPT and who can bring enthusiasm, experience and insight into shaping and leading Talking Therapies as part of an integrated model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main aims of the role is to develop and lead the service in all clinical aspects through:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing, implementing and maintaining clinical policy and pathways related to primary care mental health&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading on an integrated approach to service delivery and Talking Therapies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsibility for Clinical Governance and the audit of all clinical work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee day to day practice within the service to ensure effective and efficient clinical practice that operates within NICE guidelines and is IAPT compliant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be considered for this role you will need to have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working in mental health and or wellbeing setting at a clinical level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be BABCP accredited&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working within an IAPT Service with a good understanding of Talking Therapy and available treatment modalities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of delivering IAPT compliant clinical supervision and case management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills both written and verbal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Why Turning Point?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a leading health and social care provider with more than 300 locations across England, we take real pride in the services we offer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Across the varied regions, sectors and settings we operate within, our organisation is held together by a shared vision – and our people are connected by the same values. These include belief in potential, confidence in communication, embracing positive change and always treating each other as individuals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We run all of our services on a not-for-profit basis; instead, we invest every penny back into our services and people. We never stop believing in change for the better, and we work constantly to improve the lives of the people we support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our people bring our vision to life. So, if you are enthusiastic, motivated and committed to support others to fulfilling their potential, here at Turning Point, we don&#39;t just offer you a job – we offer you a career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;What Benefits Will I Receive?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Of course, we know it&#39;s not about the money. But that doesn&#39;t mean we don&#39;t reward our people for their invaluable work with a benefits package that includes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to Active Luton Facilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive opportunities to learn and develop, with silver accreditation from Investors in People&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;33 days’ paid holiday a year, increasing with each year of service up to 35 days. Plus the option to purchase additional holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible benefit options including cycle to work schemes and season ticket loans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive pension and life assurance schemes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee assistance programme and access to online health and wellbeing support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working patterns to support work-life balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to a wide range of discounts, including cinema tickets, grocery and high-street shopping and gym memberships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this post and would like to find out more please call Deana Kirkby National IAPT Operations Manager on 07739 206101.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We reserve the right to close this advert early if we are able to appoint to the vacancy before the advertised closed date.&lt;/p&gt;
